scanned to PDF by me.

PATHFINDERS
'If I saw further than others, it is because I was standing on the shoulders of giants,' Isaac Newton said once.
Thanks to various breakthroughs in science, people today enjoy a better quality of life. We prevent epidemics, invent new machines, and bring the world together with gadgets like the TV and computer. But these advancements did not appear magically out of nowhere. In fact, they were created by the unflagging efforti and struggles of dedicated
men of science through the ages.
The following pages tell you about some of the great scientists.
